You are building "Fetch" — a proximity-based dog social network. This is a web-based MVP demo with ALL MOCK DATA. No backend, no APIs, no database. Everything runs client-side with hardcoded mock data and React state.

TECH STACK:
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons
- next-pwa (optional, for mobile feel)
- Deploy target: Vercel

THIS IS A MOBILE-FIRST WEB APP:
- Max width: 430px, centered on desktop with a phone-frame wrapper
- All interactions are tap-based (no hover-dependent UI)
- Bottom tab navigation (fixed)
- Native app feel: full-bleed screens, no browser chrome feeling
- iOS-style transitions (slide from right for push, fade for tabs)
- Smooth 60fps animations everywhere

DESIGN SYSTEM:
- Colors:
  - Navy: #0D2137 (primary backgrounds, headers)
  - Blue: #1A7BBF (CTAs, interactive elements, links)
  - Orange: #E8913A (friend highlights, notifications, warmth)
  - Off-white: #F5F7FA (page backgrounds)
  - White: #FFFFFF (cards)
  - Charcoal: #1C2833 (primary text)
  - Grey: #7F8C8D (secondary text)
  - Light Blue: #E8F0F7 (subtle backgrounds, badges)
  - Light Orange: #FEF5E7 (friend card backgrounds)
  - Success Green: #27AE60 (confirmations)
  - Error Red: #E74C3C (destructive actions)

- Typography:
  - Font: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif (native feel)
  - Titles: 24-32px, font-weight 800
  - Headings: 18-20px, font-weight 700
  - Body: 14-15px, font-weight 400
  - Captions: 11-12px, font-weight 400, grey color
  - All caps for section labels, letter-spacing 0.05em, 11px, grey

- Spacing: Tailwind defaults (p-4 = 16px standard padding)
- Border radius: rounded-xl (12px) for cards, rounded-2xl (16px) for modals, rounded-full for avatars/pills
- Shadows: shadow-sm for cards, shadow-lg for modals/floating elements
- Cards: white background, rounded-xl, shadow-sm, p-4

MOCK DATA APPROACH:
- All mock data lives in src/data/ folder
- React state (useState/useReducer) for interactive state changes
- localStorage for persistence between page refreshes (check-in state, friends added, etc.)
- No API calls, no fetch(), no external data sources

FILE STRUCTURE:
- src/app/ — Next.js App Router pages
- src/components/ — Reusable UI components
- src/components/screens/ — Full screen components (one per "page")
- src/data/ — All mock data files
- src/hooks/ — Custom React hooks
- src/types/ — TypeScript interfaces
- src/lib/ — Utilities

CRITICAL UX RULES:
- Every tap should feel responsive (instant visual feedback)
- Use Framer Motion for all transitions and micro-interactions
- Loading states should use skeleton screens, not spinners
- Empty states should be friendly and actionable
- The app should feel REAL — like you're using a production app, not a prototype
- Dog emoji (🐕) is the app's visual signature — use sparingly but consistently